        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This example demonstrates how to run a LINQ query and then bind to the results.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following example creates two list boxes.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The first list box contains three list items.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Selecting an item from the first list box invokes the following event handler.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this example, <ph id="ph1">`Tasks`</ph> is a collection of <ph id="ph2">`Task`</ph> objects.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">`Task`</ph> class has a property named <ph id="ph2">`Priority`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This event handler runs a LINQ query that returns the collection of <ph id="ph1">`Task`</ph> objects that have the selected priority value, and then sets that as the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.DataContext%2A&gt;</ph>:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The second list box binds to that collection because its <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.ItemsControl.ItemsSource%2A&gt;</ph> value is set to <ph id="ph2">`{Binding}`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>As a result, it displays the returned collection (based on the <ph id="ph1">`myTaskTemplate`</ph><ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.DataTemplate&gt;</ph>).</source>
        </trans-unit>
